author: brane
msg: Fix some regexps in the getopt test. Hmm, it's a wonder this worked at all.
* getopt_tests.py (del_lines_res): Remove the anchors, and also match
the 'http' schema, not just 'https'.
(process_lines): Use re.match instead of re.search, and don't skip the
first character in the match string.
(run_one_test): Make the actual vs. expected output display nicer.

author: philip
msg: Fix issue 1021.  Reinstate the code that updates the entries file when
resolving conflicts (it got disabled during the access baton conversion).
* subversion/include/svn_wc.h (svn_wc_resolve_conflict): Add access baton
parameter.
* subversion/libsvn_client/resolve.c (svn_client_resolve): Open and close
an access baton.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_crawler.c (restore_file): Pass access baton to
svn_wc_resolve_conflict.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_ops.c
(resolve_conflict_on_entry): Change directory parameter from char* path
to access baton.  Reinstate the code that modifies the entry, but without
opening/closing a local access baton.
(struct resolve_callback_baton): Add access baton member.
(resolve_found_entry_callback): Retrieve and pass access baton.
(svn_wc_resolve_conflict): Add access baton parameter and store in the
callback baton.  Don't open/close a local access baton.
